===========================================================================
A) ABOUT ELSI
===========================================================================

   ELSI provides and enhances open-source software packages which solve or
   circumvent eigenvalue problems in self-consistent field calculations
   based on the Kohn-Sham density-functional theory.

   Visit the ELSI Interchange website for more information:

     http://elsi-interchange.org

   For questions, please email:

     elsi-team@duke.edu

===========================================================================
B) INSTALLATION OF ELSI
===========================================================================

   The standard installation of ELSI requires:

   *  CMake             [version 3.0.2 or newer]
   *  Fortran compiler  [with Fortran 2003 standard]
   *  C compiler        [with C99 standard]
   *  C++ compiler      [with C++11 standard]
   *  MPI library
   *  Math libraries    [BLAS, LAPACK, BLACS, and ScaLAPACK]
   *  PT-SCOTCH library [version 6.0.4 or newer]

   Installation with recent versions of Cray, GNU, IBM, Intel, and PGI
   compilers has been tested.

   For a complete description of the installation process, please refer to
   the "INSTALL" file.

===========================================================================
